sentences: In 1952, he headed Turk Murphy's Jazz Band, which included pianist Wally Rose, clarinetist Bob Helm, banjoist Dick Lammi, and tubaist Bob Short.
The band appeared on The Ed Sullivan Show twice, in 1959 and 1965.
In 1979, Robert Schulz began an eight-year stint with the band.
Murphy was the singer for the 1971 Sesame Street cartoon shorts, "The Alligator King" and "No. 9 Martian Beauty".
Murphy's band played his nightclub, Earthquake McGoons, which opened in 1960 and moved three times before closing in 1984.

sentences: Melvin Edward Alton "Turk" Murphy (December 16, 1915 – May 30, 1987) was an American trombonist and bandleader, who played traditional and Dixieland jazz.
Murphy's band played his nightclub, Earthquake McGoons, which opened in 1960 and moved three times before closing in 1984.
